The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Lalu Deb, 30, a trader, suffered hand injuries, when two unidentified men fired at him in Sarsuna on Thursday morning. Deb, a resident of the area, is undergoing treatment at a nursing home. Police suspect business rivalry was behind the attack.     Uttam Pandey, 38, was arrested in Thakurpukur on Thursday in connection with the alleged abduction of Jyotsna Bal at Hindusthan Park on September 3.    State home secretary Samar Ghosh took over as chief secretary on Thursday. G.D. Gautama took over as home secretary.    Power supply to the New Ballygunge, CN Roy Road, Picnic Garden, Sapgachi, Tiljala Road, Bediadanga Road, Topsia Road, Kusthia Road, Gulam Jilani Khan Road and Kasba Dharmatala Road areas may be disrupted from 11am to 4pm on Friday because of maintenance.    A fast-track court in Howrah on Thursday sentenced Shyamal Chatterjee, 40, to life imprisonment for killing his sister in May 2005.                                                                                                                                               
